Tshegofatso Mabasa of Orlando Pirates during the DStv Premiership 2020/21 match between Orlando Pirates and Baroka FC on the 28 November 2020 at Orlando Stadium. Sydney Mahlangu/BackpagePix JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates have left it late to salvage a point after being held to a 1-all draw by Baroka FC at Orlando Stadium.
After a goalless draw at the interval, Bagaga broke the deadlock in the opening minute of the second half after a mistake by goalkeeper Richard Ofori. READ: Orlando Pirates release eight players Despite pushing hard for an equaliser, the Sea Robbers had to wait until added time for parity. Substitute Tshegofatso Mabasa profited from a cross from fellow substitute Deon Hotto.